      {
        "paragraph_index": 3,
        "text": "### Chemistry Insights\n\n- **Amino acids** dominating the top spot reflects their immense biological relevance — they are natural chelators with both amine and carboxylate donor groups, making them ideal ligands for metal ions in biological and pharmaceutical contexts.\n- **Pyridines (azines)** and **aliphatic amines** are workhorses of coordination chemistry, offering nitrogen donors with tunable basicity across a huge structural diversity.\n- **Aza-macrocycles** (e.g., cyclam, cyclen derivatives) are notable for forming exceptionally stable complexes due to the macrocyclic effect, which is why they appear prominently despite being a more specialized class.\n\n*Source: NIST SRD-46 (ligand_card table)*",
